    // get rewritten to the OFF tint (so the off-cell background colour
    // matches the on-cell substrate), then the buffer is uploaded to the
    // renderer. The renderer keeps its own CPU mirror + diffs against it,
    // so re-uploading an identical buffer is a cheap no-op.
